entry.title: Hydrologic Outlook issued April 26 at 4:42PM MDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...WARMING TEMPERATURES WILL RESULT IN INCREASED SNOW MELT AND POTENTIAL FLOODING... Temperatures will increase through the weekend, resulting in increased snow melt in lower elevations. High temperatures for lower elevations are expected to be in the middle to upper 50s to near 60 this weekend with low temperatures only dropping to near freezing.
